[30;1m290 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m291 | [0m[35m        This method ensures that the policy weights used by the data collector are synchronized with[0m
[30;1m292 | [0m[35m        trained weights. It supports both local and remote weight updates, depending on the configur[0m
[30;1m293 | [0m[35m        data collector. The local (download) update is performed before the remote (upload) update, [0m
[30;1m294 | [0m[35m        can be transferred to the children workers from a server.[0m

[30;1m2083 | [0m[35m    def _complete_done([0m
[30;1m2084 | [0m[35m        cls, done_spec: Composite, data: TensorDictBase[0m
[30;1m2085 | [0m[35m    ) -> TensorDictBase:[0m
[30;1m2086 | [0m[35m        """Completes the data structure at step time to put missing done keys."""[0m
[30;1m2087 | [0m[35m        # by default, if a done key is missing, it is assumed that it is False[0m

[30;1m2795 | [0m[35m            # To make step_and_maybe_reset handle custom reset states, some version of TensorDictPri[0m

[30;1m42 | [0m[35m    Brax offers a vectorized and differentiable simulation framework based on Jax.[0m
[30;1m43 | [0m[35m    TorchRL's wrapper incurs some overhead for the jax-to-torch conversion,[0m
[30;1m44 | [0m[35m    but computational graphs can still be built on top of the simulated trajectories,[0m
[30;1m45 | [0m[35m    allowing for backpropagation through the rollout.[0m
[30;1m46 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m47 | [0m[35m    GitHub: https://github.com/google/brax[0m

[30;1m23 | [0m[35mclass KLControllerBase(abc.ABC):[0m
[30;1m24 | [0m[35m    """Base class for KL controllers.[0m
[30;1m25 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m26 | [0m[35m    Each controller must implement an update method that takes the current KL value and[0m
[30;1m27 | [0m[35m    the number of steps and updates the kl_coef attribute of the wrapped model,[0m

[30;1m799 | [0m[35m            of the stored trajectory) and on the right (end of the stored trajectory).[0m
